<br>
As new Knight Distinguished I would like to get everyone familiar with our Merit program.  Our previous Distinguished, Slaydark, has explained it so precisely, I'm stealing his following post that was on the Officers Message Board *chuckles at Slay*<br>
<br>
All of us have experienced or witnessed moments when a character has displayed acts of courage, prowess, or achievements we admire.  The Awards program helps us to identify, recognize and congratulate those who distinguish themselves in a manner that merits an award or medal. <br>
The Awards program also helps to inspire and encourage members of The Knights of Valor to work/assist one another and...to promote distinguishable traits and characteristics we recognize as honorable, helpfull, brave, heroic, journeymen, fidelity, and valorous.<br>
<br>
Any full citizen member, (30 days KoV), may recommend or nominate any other citizen member for an award(recommend) or medal(nominate). The member must either inform an officer of such recommendation/ nomination or contact the Awards Chair, (Knight Distinguished), so that an investigation may be conducted.  When one submits a recommendation or nomination, it must include the location, time, witnesses, action/conduct to be investigated, and the award/medal that would be conferred. The awards chair would than assign an officer or (2) officers, (for Medals), to conduct an investigation and submit a report to the Awards Chair for review, (here the Knight Distinguished reviews to see that the criteria has been met and discusses such with investigating officers), and submission/post  to the High Council, for its onsideration/approval.<br>
<br>
Please keep in mind, when gaming with others in group or camp, to consider actions or achievements that you recognize in your guildmates.  If you do not send in a recommendation or nomination, than that person is not recognized by his peers in our awards ceremony.  This program is participation based.  And you may chose to ignore or not participate at all. But, as the High Council has <br>
discussed, determined, and voted to establish it,... This program is here to enhance recognition..., motivate character..., provide color..., and establish unity, for The Knights of Valor.  The Knight Distinguished is it promotional officer and guide, but it only works, if YOU Do ! Many have worked hard to attain, sacrificed much to assist, and intelligently implore tactics and strategies to overcome adversities we face on Norrath daily.  Please do not let those instances go without acknowledgment.<br>
<br>
Awards and Medals:<br>
<br>
*Awards* are identified as Legions, Expeditionaries, or Ribbons. These do not require the degree of scrutiny to attain as does a (medal).  A single officer could investigate submit report to the awards chair for review and submission.  Awards are recommendations and are as follows;<br>
<br>
Legion of Goodwill - member who assists other members<br>
Legion of Honor - member who adheres to personal honesty and integrity<br>
Legion of Courage - member who exemplifies bravery and courage<br>
Legion of Fortitude - member who protects or enhances the interests of the guild, Its charter, Its codes, or its bylaws.<br>
Legion of Merit - member who brings distinction or recognition to the guild (recommended by others outside the guild).<br>
<br>
Knight Expeditionary -member who participates in 5 guild raids/events<br>
Joint Expeditionary - member who participates in 5 other guild Rds/Events<br>
Venture Expeditionary - member who participates in assisting  another member in his/her epic quest to its Conclusion. <br>
<br>
Mastery of Arts - member who achieves 150 skill rating in a <br>
particular trade skill.<br>
Knights of Valor Ribbon - Full Citizen Knight of Valor (30 days)<br>
<br>
*Medals* are recognized as Commendations of Higher Deeds/Actions.<br>
Medals require a higher degree of scrutiny and therefore assigned to (2) officers for investigation.  The Officers put together a detailed report of the nominee, (medals are nominated), and submit report to the Awards Chair for review, and concurrence.  It is than submitted to the High Council for review, consideration, and determined presentation.  Medals are Higher Forms of Recognition. Attainment should be carefully guarded, so as to not demote or trivialize its <br>
proper intent.<br>
<br>
 The Medals are as follows;<br>
<br>
Medal of Fidelity - Member who has been in good standing for 9 consecutive months.<br>
<br>
Medal of Chivalry - Member who has been recognized for valor, gallantry, honor or charity, outside of the guild.<br>
<br>
Medal of Gallantry - Member who has distinguished him/her self as hero or lifesaver of a group or situation.<br>
<br>
Medal of Valor - Member who displays prowess above and beyond the call of duty. Identifies individuals use of ablilities, tactics and strategies to overcome a foe.<br>
<br>
Meritorious Unit Commendation - Group of (5) or more knights who as a unit distinguish themselves in battle showing determination, gallantry, valor, and espirit de corps.<br>
<br>
The Last Recognition Is The Supreme Honor Of Any Member of The KoV.<br>
<br>
The Sword of The Virtuous<br>
Obtained by Achievment of (5) of the 4 medals listed. <br>
(one with a 2nd star)<br>
<br>
 Please check our Medals &amp; Merits section at the KOV main screen. If you have any questions please contact me in game or via email tzbaby@hotmail.com.  <br>
